lua-pica
--------
Lua library to handle PICA+ data

Installation
------------
Copy the contents of the 'src' directory into a location on your LUA_PATH.

Use
---

    require 'pica'

    input = io.read("*all")
    record = PicaRecord.parse( input )

    eki = record.first('007G') -- get the first matching field or nil
    if eki then
        eki = eki['c']..eki['0'] -- get subfield values or ''
    end

Feedback and updates
--------------------
please visit https://github.com/nichtich/lua-pica

